text:
Happy nice folks;

Quit decent food and a reasonable price.

If you are in the neighborhood give it a shot.

Almost a perfect pre-experience. I did an order to go on a Monday lunch. The place was easy to find. As you get in, you're faced with this beautiful well decorated quiet ambience typical Oriental. 

I didn't have much time so I was hoping they were quick on the order. The lady immediately showed me lunch specials so here's what I got: 

- hot and sour soup...DELICIOUS!! For some reasons I got two of those (maybe I didn't express myself clearly);
- fried rice was also good and even more tasty with some soy sauce on it (eat it hot cause it tends to dry up);
- sweet and sour pork...and here's why I don't give 5 stars: it was very mushy and pretty tasteless even with additional sauce. Too bad. It's one of my favorite dishes of the Chinese cuisine. 

Service was quick. I would say they probably took less than 10 minutes. I would go back, just not for the sweet and sour pork.
